# Architecture

`asm` is a family asset-management app: Drift (SQLite) + Riverpod + go_router + fl_chart.

## Layers (dependencies point downward only)

- `lib/features/**` — UI (pages/widgets). May depend on core + domain + l10n.
- `lib/core/**` — providers, router, theme, notifications, backup, constants.
- `lib/data/**` — Drift database (`db/`) and repositories (`repositories/`).
- `lib/domain/**` — pure Dart: calculators, currency, forecast, enums. NO Flutter/Drift imports.
- `lib/l10n/**` — generated localizations.

## Rules

- UI never touches the `AppDatabase` directly; go through a repository (exposed via a Riverpod provider in `lib/core/providers/providers.dart`).
- Domain code stays pure and unit-testable: no `package:flutter`, no `package:drift`.
- New cross-cutting non-localized strings go in `lib/core/app_constants.dart`; numeric defaults like FX fallbacks in `lib/domain/currency/fx_defaults.dart`.
- Run `flutter analyze` (must be clean) and `flutter test` before considering a change done. Regenerate Drift code with `dart run build_runner build` after editing `lib/data/db/tables.dart`.
